body.description: Currently, our diaper is not 100% compostable. To our knowledge, there are no diapers in the market that are 100% Certified Compostable. We will continue to strive to create a diaper that is 100% compostable with all elements being certified and being able to break down in a commercial composting setting. We understand not all customers have access to a service that compost diapers but our wish is to continue to align with partners who strive to create more opportunities for these diapers to be composted. Until then, we will continue to provide a diaper that works and works well with the best eco friendly materials on the market that are safe for your baby and safer for the environment.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Our Babies, Our Planet Nurture baby wet wipes are a better way to think about the materials we put on our skin and our baby’s skin. Our mission is to leave the Earth a better place than when we found it, which is why we hand-picked our wet wipe ingredients, avoiding harsh chemicals. Nurture wipes are dermatologically tested, hypoallergenic and made with premium ingredients that do not cause skin irritation. Formulated without perfumes, dyes, parabens, phthalates, or alcohol. These are the perfect wipes for hands, face, and baby’s bottom. When it is time to change and clean your little one, Nurture wet wipes are strong and durable to get the job done, yet soft and gentle on baby’s skin. We never test our wipes on animals, so you can feel good about using a product that respects the Earth and our animals the way you do! You can even use our wipes to clean your fur babies when baths are not an option! We wanted a production partner who shared our environmental vision and could source the certified materials required for the creation of Nurture diapers. As we narrowed our list of potential production partners, a member of our BioBag European team suggested we meet with ABENA in Denmark, as this company’s environmental profile would be a perfect fit for the task ahead. We went. We were blown away with their state-of-the-art facility, a plant run on 100% clean and renewable wind energy, and their management’s enthusiasm for the concept of creating the Nurture brand. Let’s make the change together and leave the world a better place than we left it. Join us on our mission to reshape how we think about diapers and diaper disposal. Nurture diapers and baby wet wipes are brought to you by your friends at BioBag! We are not some large, petroleum-based diaper and wipe company. We are, instead, a small, dedicated group of moms and dads just like you who saw an opportunity to make baby products without using harsh chemicals or ingredients.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The diapers hold up overnight with our tube-fed baby! They fit perfectly around the legs and have strong fasteners that stand up to her rolling around during the night! We also love the compostable packaging.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These fit nicely and seems to be very absorbent!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked well and more eco friendly
reviews.reviewText: These worked great for our little one! We were really struggling with wanting a diaper that worked for our baby while weighing the environmental impact of mainstream diaper brands. Kept mess in and reduced our footprint - would definitely recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great diapers for our baby
reviews.reviewText: We love Nurture diapers. I use these because I’m part of a compostable diapering service, I prefer these to the other compostable options. Our baby has the best chunky thighs, and these fit well around his many rolls. We’ve had the least amount of blowouts in these diapers of any other. Fits true to size.I just wish they had a subscription service!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than expected
reviews.reviewText: I was worried a natural brand may not be here to absorb as much. But I was pleasantly surprised. The diapers held up overnight play my seven month old. He wears a size 2 in Pampers and Huggies. We got a size 3 in this brand and although they are slightly larger they fit well. They pretty much just run a little higher in the waist so I thought them over in the front. My son is about 18 pounds and 24 inches long.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Gave my baby a rash
reviews.reviewText: I normally use Dyper, thought I'd give this a try since it was next day delivery. My baby started developing a rash after two days! I went back to Dyper and her rash diminished. They also leak but that wasn't even the big issue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Pee indicators already dark!
reviews.reviewText: I liked these diapers for sustainability but all the pee indicators were already greenish before we started using them! Also she def leaked out of them overnight so needed spoosies booster pad overnight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great fit, but limited absorbency
reviews.reviewText: These diapers fit our baby well where others haven’t, but unfortunately, the lower absorbency requires frequent changing with our ‘super soaker’ and doesn’t seem to keep her dry overnight. Not quite as soft as Earth&Eden diapers, but no reaction to materials used.
